Topic 1: Operational Security  

Resource 1: 

Xingze Zhao, 2025. Impact of informality on operational security in emerging markets. Sciencedirect.com 

Type: Peer-review 

Synopsis: It looks at how informal practices affect operational security in emerging firms. In emerging markets, the prevalence of informal economic activities is a well documented characteristic, with many firms initiating operations without formal registration or legal status. The motivations for such choices typically center around avoiding the high costs and bureaucratic hurdles associated with formalization which can be prohibitive for startups and small firms. 

Link: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article 

Relevance: 5/5 - Addresses the struggles of start up as they balance their financial situation and security. 

Resource 2:  

Citation: Jessica Butel, (2023). Impact of organizational security certification on operational security: Examining the red tape. It examines the relationship between operational security and organization security compliance that is driven by requirement to achieve a security certification or accreditation. 

Type: Academic Article 

Synopsis: Reviews how compliance demands can affect operational security.  

Link: https://comp.mga.edu/static/media/doctoralpapers/ 

Relevance: 5/5 - It goes over the standard of operation security. 

Resource 3: 

Citation: ISACA Journal, (2021). The evolution of Security Operations and strategies for building an Effective SOC. The new development of AI and other technologies will lead to high impact cyberattacks.  

Type: Media Article 

Synopsis: Evaluates the importance of SOC is evolution and implementation. 

Link: https://www.isaca.org/resources/isaca-journal/issues/2021/volume-5/the-evolution-of-security-operations-and-strategies-for-building-an-effective-soc 

Relevance: 5/5 - SOC implementation is important for any company. 

 

Resource 4: 

Citation: Verizon white paper, (2024) Holistic approach securing Operational Technologies. Industry perspectives on combining IT/OT and securing operational systems. 

Type: White papers 

Synopsis: Talks about the us the dangers of outdated systems and the need for integration of secure operational systems.  

Link: https://info.verizonenterprise.com/rs/157-IPW-846/images/Holistic_approach_towards_securing_Operational_Technologies_%28OT%29_Whitepaper.pdf 

Relevance: 5/5 -Talks about the need for the integration of SOC technology on out dated systems. 

Topic 2: Ethical Hacking 

Resource 1: 

Citation: Yaacoub, J.-P. A., H., Salman, O., & Chehab. (2023). Ethical Hacking for IoT: Security issues, challenges, solutions and recommendations. 

Type: peer-reviewed 

Synapsis: Talks about the dangers of the compromise IoT and network devices. 

Link: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2667345223000238? 

Relevance: 5/5 - Talks about the dangers of being vulnerable from your IoT and network devices. 

Resource 2: 

Citation: Berger, H., & Jones, A. (2016). Cybersecurity & ethical hacking for SMEs. 

Type: blog-post 

Synapsis: Talks about case study-driven guidance on introducing ethical hacking in smaller enterprises using open source tools. 

Link: https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2925995.2926016 

Relevance: 5/5 - It is import to secure your network no matter how small it is. 

Resource 3: 

Citation: McGrew, W. (2015). I Hunt Penetration Testers: OPSEC for Pentesters. DEF CON 23. 

Type: Youtube  

Synopsis: Operational Security for penetration tester, communication Data Security Issues. Illustrating and classifying risks posed by your tools. 

Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pSGAu4PZ7bw 

 Relevance: 4/5 - Practice focused on OPSEC guidance for ethical work. 

Resource 4: 

Citation: Alhamed, M. Alhussain, T., & Alshamrani, A (2023). A review on penetration testing in networks. 

Type: Peer-review 

Synopsis: 39 studies on network pentesting tools, methods types of attacks and remediation. 

Link: https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/13/12/6986 

Relevance: 5/5 - shows methodologies and the practice of pen-testing 
